{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"You might be wondering why I'm wearing sunglasses,"},{"time":2000,"text":"and one answer to that is, because I'm here to talk about glamour."},{"time":7000,"text":"So, we all think we know what glamour is. Here it is."},{"time":10000,"text":"It's glamorous movie stars, like Marlene Dietrich."},{"time":13000,"text":"And it comes in a male form, too --"},{"time":15000,"text":"very glamorous."},{"time":17000,"text":"Not only can he shoot, drive, drink -- you know, he drinks wine,"},{"time":21000,"text":"there actually is a little wine in there --"},{"time":23000,"text":"and of course, always wears a tuxedo."},{"time":26000,"text":"But I think that glamour actually has a much broader meaning --"},{"time":30000,"text":"one that is true for the movie stars and the fictional characters,"},{"time":34000,"text":"but also comes in other forms."}]},{"cues":[{"time":36000,"text":"A magazine?"},{"time":38000,"text":"Well, it's certainly not this one."},{"time":40000,"text":"This is the least glamorous magazine on the newsstand -- it's all about sex tips."},{"time":43000,"text":"Sex tips are not glamorous."},{"time":45000,"text":"And Drew Barrymore, for all her wonderful charm,"},{"time":48000,"text":"is not glamorous either."},{"time":50000,"text":"But there is a glamour of industry."},{"time":52000,"text":"This is Margaret Bourke-White's --"},{"time":54000,"text":"one of her pictures she did."},{"time":56000,"text":"Fantastic, glamorous pictures"},{"time":59000,"text":"of steel mills and paper mills and all kinds of glamorous industrial places."},{"time":63000,"text":"And there's the mythic glamour"},{"time":65000,"text":"of the garage entrepreneur."},{"time":67000,"text":"This is the Hewlett-Packard garage."},{"time":69000,"text":"We know everyone who starts a business in a garage"},{"time":72000,"text":"ends up founding Hewlett-Packard."},{"time":75000,"text":"There's the glamour of physics."},{"time":77000,"text":"What could be more glamorous than understanding the entire universe,"},{"time":79000,"text":"grand unification? And, by the way, it helps if you're Brian Greene --"},{"time":83000,"text":"he has other kinds of glamour."}]},{"cues":[{"time":85000,"text":"And there is, of course, this glamour."},{"time":87000,"text":"This is very, very glamorous: the glamour of outer space --"},{"time":90000,"text":"and not the alien-style glamour,"},{"time":93000,"text":"but the nice, clean, early '60s version."},{"time":96000,"text":"So what do we mean by glamour?"},{"time":98000,"text":"Well, one thing you can do if you want to know what glamour means"},{"time":102000,"text":"is you can look in the dictionary."},{"time":104000,"text":"And it actually helps a lot more if you look in a very old dictionary,"},{"time":107000,"text":"in this case the 1913 dictionary."},{"time":109000,"text":"Because for centuries, glamour had a very particular meaning,"},{"time":114000,"text":"and the word was actually used differently from the way we think of it."},{"time":119000,"text":"You had \"a\" glamour."},{"time":121000,"text":"It wasn't glamour as a quality -- you \"cast a glamour.\""},{"time":123000,"text":"Glamour was a literal magic spell."},{"time":126000,"text":"Not a metaphorical one, the way we use it today,"},{"time":128000,"text":"but a literal magic spell associated with witches and gypsies"},{"time":132000,"text":"and to some extent, Celtic magic."},{"time":135000,"text":"And over the years, around the turn of the 20th century,"},{"time":138000,"text":"it started to take on this other kind of deception --"},{"time":144000,"text":"this definition for any artificial interest in, or association with,"},{"time":149000,"text":"an object through which it appears delusively magnified or glorified."},{"time":154000,"text":"But still, glamour is an illusion."},{"time":156000,"text":"Glamour is a magic spell."},{"time":159000,"text":"And there's something dangerous about glamour"},{"time":161000,"text":"throughout most of history. When the witches cast a magic spell"},{"time":165000,"text":"on you, it was not in your self-interest --"},{"time":167000,"text":"it was to get you to act against your interest."}]},{"cues":[{"time":169000,"text":"Well of course, in the 20th century,"},{"time":171000,"text":"glamour came to have this different meaning associated with Hollywood."},{"time":175000,"text":"And this is Hedy Lamarr."},{"time":177000,"text":"Hedy Lamarr said, \"Anyone can look glamorous,"},{"time":179000,"text":"all you have to do is sit there and look stupid.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":182000,"text":"But in fact, with all due respect to Hedy --"},{"time":187000,"text":"about whom we'll hear more later -- there's a lot more to it."},{"time":191000,"text":"There was a tremendous amount of technical achievement"},{"time":194000,"text":"associated with creating this Hollywood glamour."},{"time":196000,"text":"There were scores of retouchers and lighting experts and make-up experts."},{"time":200000,"text":"You can go to the museum of Hollywood history in Hollywood"},{"time":203000,"text":"and see Max Factor's special rooms that he painted different colors"},{"time":206000,"text":"depending on the complexion of the star he was going to make up."},{"time":210000,"text":"So you've got this highly stylized portrait of something"},{"time":213000,"text":"that was not entirely of this earth -- it was a portrait of a star."},{"time":216000,"text":"And actually, we see glamorized photos of stars all the time --"},{"time":220000,"text":"they call them false color."}]},{"cues":[{"time":222000,"text":"Glamour is a form of falsification,"},{"time":226000,"text":"but falsification to achieve a particular purpose."},{"time":229000,"text":"It may be to illuminate the star; it may be to sell a film."},{"time":233000,"text":"And it involves a great deal of technique."},{"time":235000,"text":"It's not -- glamour is not something --"},{"time":237000,"text":"you don't wake up in the morning glamorous. I don't care who you are."},{"time":240000,"text":"Even Nicole Kidman doesn't wake up in the morning glamorous."},{"time":243000,"text":"There is a process of \"idealization, glorification and dramatization,\""},{"time":247000,"text":"and it's not just the case for people."},{"time":249000,"text":"Glamour doesn't have to be people."},{"time":251000,"text":"Architectural photography --"},{"time":253000,"text":"Julius Schulman, who has talked about transfiguration,"},{"time":256000,"text":"took this fabulous, famous picture of the Kauffman House."},{"time":259000,"text":"Architectural photography is extremely glamorous."},{"time":262000,"text":"It puts you into this special, special world."},{"time":266000,"text":"This is Alex Ross's comic book art,"},{"time":269000,"text":"which appears to be extremely realistic,"},{"time":271000,"text":"as part of his style is he gives you a kind of realism in his comic art."},{"time":276000,"text":"Except that light doesn't work this way in the real world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":279000,"text":"When you stack people in rows,"},{"time":281000,"text":"the ones in the background look smaller than the ones in the foreground --"},{"time":284000,"text":"but not in the world of glamour."},{"time":287000,"text":"What glamour is all about -- I took this from a blurb"},{"time":290000,"text":"in the table of contents of New York magazine,"},{"time":293000,"text":"which was telling us that glamour is back --"},{"time":295000,"text":"glamour is all about transcending the everyday."},{"time":298000,"text":"And I think that that's starting to get at what the core"},{"time":301000,"text":"that combines all sorts of glamour is."},{"time":304000,"text":"This is Filippino Lippi's 1543 portrait of Saint Apollonia."},{"time":309000,"text":"And I don't know who she is either,"},{"time":311000,"text":"but this is the [16th] century equivalent of a supermodel."},{"time":314000,"text":"It's a very glamorous portrait."},{"time":316000,"text":"Why is it glamorous?"},{"time":318000,"text":"It's glamorous, first, because she is beautiful --"},{"time":320000,"text":"but that does not make you glamorous,"},{"time":322000,"text":"that only makes you beautiful."},{"time":324000,"text":"She is graceful, she is mysterious and she is transcendent,"},{"time":329000,"text":"and those are the central qualities of glamour."},{"time":331000,"text":"You don't see her eyes; they're looking downward."},{"time":335000,"text":"She's not looking away from you exactly,"},{"time":337000,"text":"but you have to mentally imagine her world."},{"time":341000,"text":"She's encouraging you to contemplate this higher world"},{"time":345000,"text":"to which she belongs, where she can be completely tranquil"},{"time":348000,"text":"while holding the iron instruments of her death by torture."},{"time":352000,"text":"Mel Gibson's \"Passion Of The Christ\" -- not glamorous."},{"time":355000,"text":"That's glamour:"},{"time":357000,"text":"that's Michelangelo's \"Pieta,\" where Mary is the same age as Jesus"},{"time":360000,"text":"and they're both awfully happy and pleasant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":363000,"text":"Glamour invites us to live in a different world."},{"time":366000,"text":"It has to simultaneously be mysterious, a little bit distant --"},{"time":370000,"text":"that's why, often in these glamour shots,"},{"time":372000,"text":"the person is not looking at the audience,"},{"time":374000,"text":"it's why sunglasses are glamorous --"},{"time":377000,"text":"but also not so far above us that we can't identify with the person."},{"time":381000,"text":"In some sense, there has to be something like us."},{"time":385000,"text":"So as I say, in religious art, you know, God is not glamorous."},{"time":388000,"text":"God cannot be glamorous because God is omnipotent,"},{"time":391000,"text":"omniscient -- too far above us."},{"time":393000,"text":"And yet you will see in religious art, saints or the Virgin Mary"},{"time":396000,"text":"will often be portrayed -- not always -- in glamorous forms."},{"time":399000,"text":"As I said earlier, glamour does not have to be about people,"},{"time":403000,"text":"but it has to have this transcendent quality."},{"time":406000,"text":"What is it about Superman?"},{"time":408000,"text":"Aside from Alex Ross's style, which is very glamorous,"},{"time":410000,"text":"one thing about Superman is he makes you believe that a man can fly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":414000,"text":"Glamour is all about transcending this world"},{"time":417000,"text":"and getting to an idealized, perfect place."},{"time":421000,"text":"And this is one reason that modes of transportation"},{"time":425000,"text":"tend to be extremely glamorous."},{"time":427000,"text":"The less experience we have with them,"},{"time":429000,"text":"the more glamorous they are."},{"time":431000,"text":"So you can do a glamorized picture of a car,"},{"time":434000,"text":"but you can't do a glamorized picture of traffic."},{"time":436000,"text":"You can do a glamorized picture of an airplane, but not the inside."},{"time":440000,"text":"The notion is that it's going to transport you,"},{"time":442000,"text":"and the story is not about, you know, the guy in front of you in the airplane,"},{"time":446000,"text":"who has this nasty little kid, or the big cough."},{"time":450000,"text":"The story is about where you're arriving,"},{"time":452000,"text":"or thinking about where you're arriving."},{"time":454000,"text":"And this sense of being transported"},{"time":456000,"text":"is one reason that we have glamour styling."},{"time":460000,"text":"This sort of streamlining styling is not just glamorous"},{"time":464000,"text":"because we associate it with movies of that period, but because,"},{"time":468000,"text":"in it's streamlining, it transports us from the everyday."}]},{"cues":[{"time":471000,"text":"The same thing -- arches are very glamorous."},{"time":474000,"text":"Arches with stained glass -- even more glamorous."},{"time":477000,"text":"Staircases that curve away from you are glamorous."},{"time":480000,"text":"I happen to find that particular staircase picture very glamorous"},{"time":483000,"text":"because, to me, it captures the whole promise"},{"time":485000,"text":"of the academic contemplative life --"},{"time":488000,"text":"but maybe that's because I went to Princeton."},{"time":490000,"text":"Anyway, skylines are super glamorous,"},{"time":493000,"text":"city streets -- not so glamorous."},{"time":495000,"text":"You know, when you get, actually to this town it has reality."},{"time":498000,"text":"The horizon, the open road, is very, very glamorous."},{"time":502000,"text":"There are few things more glamorous than the horizon --"},{"time":505000,"text":"except, possibly, multiple horizons."},{"time":509000,"text":"Of course, here you don't feel the cold, or the heat --"},{"time":514000,"text":"you just see the possibilities."},{"time":516000,"text":"In order to pull glamour off, you need this Renaissance quality"},{"time":520000,"text":"of sprezzatura, which is a term coined by Castiglione"},{"time":525000,"text":"in his book, \"The Book Of The Courtier.\""},{"time":527000,"text":"There's the not-glamorous version of what it looks like today,"},{"time":530000,"text":"after a few centuries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":532000,"text":"And sprezzatura is the art that conceals art."},{"time":536000,"text":"It makes things look effortless."},{"time":538000,"text":"You don't think about how Nicole Kidman is maneuvering that dress --"},{"time":542000,"text":"she just looks completely natural."},{"time":544000,"text":"And I remember reading, after the Lara Croft movies,"},{"time":547000,"text":"how Angelina Jolie would go home completely black and blue."},{"time":551000,"text":"Of course, they covered that with make-up,"},{"time":553000,"text":"because Lara Croft did all those same stunts --"},{"time":555000,"text":"but she doesn't get black and blue, because she has sprezzatura."},{"time":559000,"text":"\"To conceal all art and make whatever is done or said appear to be without effort\":"},{"time":564000,"text":"And this is one of the critical aspects of glamour."},{"time":567000,"text":"Glamour is about editing."},{"time":569000,"text":"How do you create the sense of transcendence,"},{"time":571000,"text":"the sense of evoking a perfect world?"},{"time":574000,"text":"The sense of, you know, life could be better, I could join this --"},{"time":578000,"text":"I could be a perfect person, I could join this perfect world."},{"time":580000,"text":"We don't tell you all the grubby details."}]},{"cues":[{"time":583000,"text":"Now, this was kindly lent to me by Jeff Bezos, from last year."},{"time":587000,"text":"This is underneath Jeff's desk."},{"time":589000,"text":"This is what the real world of computers,"},{"time":592000,"text":"lamps, electrical appliances of all kinds, looks like."},{"time":596000,"text":"But if you look in a catalog --"},{"time":598000,"text":"particularly a catalog of modern, beautiful objects for your home --"},{"time":601000,"text":"it looks like this."},{"time":603000,"text":"There are no cords."},{"time":605000,"text":"Look next time you get these catalogs in your mail --"},{"time":608000,"text":"you can usually figure out where they hid the cord."},{"time":611000,"text":"But there's always this illusion that if you buy this lamp,"},{"time":614000,"text":"you will live in a world without cords. (Laughter)"},{"time":617000,"text":"And the same thing is true of, if you buy this laptop"},{"time":620000,"text":"or you buy this computer -- and even in these wireless eras,"},{"time":623000,"text":"you don't get to live in the world without cords."},{"time":625000,"text":"You have to have mystery and you have to have grace."},{"time":629000,"text":"And there she is -- Grace."},{"time":631000,"text":"This is the most glamorous picture, I think, ever."},{"time":633000,"text":"Part of the thing is that, in \"Rear Window,\""},{"time":636000,"text":"the question is, is she too glamorous to live in his world?"},{"time":639000,"text":"And the answer is no, but of course it's really just a movie."}]},{"cues":[{"time":642000,"text":"Here's Hedy Lamarr again."},{"time":644000,"text":"And, you know, this kind of head covering is extremely glamorous"},{"time":647000,"text":"because, like sunglasses, it conceals and reveals at the same time."},{"time":651000,"text":"Translucence is glamorous --"},{"time":653000,"text":"that's why all these people wear pearls."},{"time":655000,"text":"It's why barware is glamorous. Glamour is translucent --"},{"time":659000,"text":"not transparent, not opaque."},{"time":661000,"text":"It invites us into the world"},{"time":663000,"text":"but it doesn't give us a completely clear picture."},{"time":667000,"text":"And I think if Grace Kelly is the most glamorous person,"},{"time":670000,"text":"maybe a spiral staircase with glass block may be the most glamorous interior shot,"},{"time":676000,"text":"because a spiral staircase is incredibly glamorous."},{"time":679000,"text":"It has that sense of going up and away,"},{"time":683000,"text":"and yet you never think about how you would really trip"},{"time":686000,"text":"if you were -- particularly going down."},{"time":688000,"text":"And of course glass block has that sense of translucence."},{"time":691000,"text":"So, this session's supposed to be about pure pleasure"},{"time":695000,"text":"but glamour's really partly about meaning."},{"time":698000,"text":"All individuals and all cultures have ideals"},{"time":701000,"text":"that cannot possibly be realized in reality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":705000,"text":"They have contradictions,"},{"time":707000,"text":"they uphold principles that are incommensurable with each other --"},{"time":710000,"text":"whatever it is -- and yet these ideals give meaning and purpose"},{"time":713000,"text":"to our lives as cultures and as individuals."},{"time":716000,"text":"And the way we deal with that is we displace them --"},{"time":720000,"text":"we put them into a golden world, an imagined world,"},{"time":723000,"text":"an age of heroes, the world to come."},{"time":726000,"text":"And in the life of an individual, we often associate that with some object."},{"time":730000,"text":"The white picket fence, the perfect house."},{"time":734000,"text":"The perfect kitchen -- no bills on the counter in the perfect kitchen."},{"time":737000,"text":"You know, you buy that Viking range, this is what your kitchen will look like."},{"time":740000,"text":"The perfect love life -- symbolized by the perfect necklace,"},{"time":743000,"text":"the perfect diamond ring."},{"time":745000,"text":"The perfect getaway in your perfect car."},{"time":747000,"text":"This is an interior design firm that is literally called Utopia."},{"time":751000,"text":"The perfect office --"},{"time":753000,"text":"again, no cords, as far as I can tell."},{"time":755000,"text":"And certainly, no, it doesn't look a thing like my office."},{"time":758000,"text":"I mean, there's no paper on the desk."},{"time":760000,"text":"We want this golden world."},{"time":762000,"text":"And some people get rich enough,"},{"time":764000,"text":"and if they have their ideals -- in a sort of domestic sense,"},{"time":768000,"text":"they get to acquire their perfect world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":770000,"text":"Dean Koontz built this fabulous home theater, which is --"},{"time":773000,"text":"I don't think accidentally -- in Art Deco style."},{"time":777000,"text":"That symbolizes this sense of being safe and at home."},{"time":780000,"text":"This is not always good, because what is your perfect world?"},{"time":783000,"text":"What is your ideal, and also, what has been edited out?"},{"time":786000,"text":"Is it something important?"},{"time":788000,"text":"\"The Matrix\" is a movie that is all about glamour."},{"time":791000,"text":"I could do a whole talk on \"The Matrix\" and glamour."},{"time":793000,"text":"It was criticized for glamorizing violence,"},{"time":797000,"text":"because, look -- sunglasses and those long coats, and, of course,"},{"time":802000,"text":"they could walk up walls and do all these kinds of things"},{"time":804000,"text":"that are impossible in the real world."},{"time":806000,"text":"This is another Margaret Bourke-White photo."},{"time":808000,"text":"This is from Soviet Union. Attractive."},{"time":810000,"text":"I mean, look how happy the people are, and good-looking too."},{"time":814000,"text":"You know, we're marching toward Utopia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":817000,"text":"I'm not a fan of PETA, but I think this is a great ad."},{"time":820000,"text":"Because what they're doing is they're saying,"},{"time":822000,"text":"your coat's not so glamorous, what's been edited out is something important."},{"time":826000,"text":"But actually, what's even more important"},{"time":828000,"text":"than remembering what's been edited out is thinking, are the ideals good?"},{"time":832000,"text":"Because glamour can be very totalitarian and deceptive."},{"time":836000,"text":"And it's not just a matter of glamorizing cleaning your floor."},{"time":839000,"text":"This is from \"Triumph Of The Will\" --"},{"time":841000,"text":"brilliant editing to cut together things."},{"time":843000,"text":"There's a glamour shot."},{"time":845000,"text":"National Socialism is all about glamour."},{"time":847000,"text":"It was a very aesthetic ideology."},{"time":849000,"text":"It was all about cleaning up Germany, and the West, and the world,"},{"time":852000,"text":"and ridding it of anything unglamorous."},{"time":854000,"text":"So glamour can be dangerous."}]},{"cues":[{"time":856000,"text":"I think glamour has a genuine appeal, has a genuine value."},{"time":859000,"text":"I'm not against glamour."},{"time":861000,"text":"But there's a kind of wonder in the stuff that gets edited away in the cords of life."},{"time":866000,"text":"And there is both a way to avoid the dangers of glamour"},{"time":870000,"text":"and a way to broaden your appreciation of it."},{"time":872000,"text":"And that's to take Isaac Mizrahi's advice"},{"time":875000,"text":"and confront the manipulation of it all,"},{"time":877000,"text":"and sort of admit that manipulation is something that we enjoy,"},{"time":882000,"text":"but also enjoy how it happens."},{"time":884000,"text":"And here's Hedy Lamarr."},{"time":886000,"text":"She's very glamorous but, you know, she invented spread-spectrum technology."},{"time":889000,"text":"So she's even more glamorous if you know that she really wasn't stupid,"},{"time":892000,"text":"even though she thought she could look stupid."}]},{"cues":[{"time":894000,"text":"David Hockney talks about how the appreciation of this"},{"time":898000,"text":"very glamorous painting is heightened if you think about"},{"time":901000,"text":"the fact that it takes two weeks to paint this splash,"},{"time":905000,"text":"which only took a fraction of a second to happen."},{"time":907000,"text":"There is a book out in the bookstore --"},{"time":910000,"text":"it's called \"Symphony In Steel,\""},{"time":912000,"text":"and it's about the stuff that's hidden under the skin of the Disney Center."},{"time":915000,"text":"And that has a fascination."},{"time":917000,"text":"It's not necessarily glamorous, but unveiling the glamour has an appeal."},{"time":920000,"text":"There's a wonderful book called \"Crowns\""},{"time":923000,"text":"that's all these glamour pictures of black women in their church hats."},{"time":927000,"text":"And there's a quote from one of these women, and she talks about,"},{"time":930000,"text":"\"As a little girl, I'd admire women at church with beautiful hats."},{"time":933000,"text":"They looked like beautiful dolls, like they'd just stepped out of a magazine."},{"time":937000,"text":"But I also knew how hard they worked all week."},{"time":940000,"text":"Sometimes under those hats there's a lot of joy and a lot of sorrow.\""},{"time":944000,"text":"And, actually, you get more appreciation for glamour"},{"time":947000,"text":"when you realize what went into creating it."},{"time":950000,"text":"Thank you."}]}]}